      "answer_index": 0,
      "question_id": "101",
      "answer": "A stack operates on a Last-In-First-Out principle. Elements are pushed onto the top and popped from the top. Common applications include expression parsing, undo/redo functionality, and tracking function calls in the call stack. A queue operates on a First-In-First-Out principle where elements are enqueued at the back and dequeued from the front. Queues are used in task scheduling, breadth-first search algorithms, and printer job queues.",
